-- Russia 2011 Mortgage Loans Reach Record Volume, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-02-13T05:16:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/russia-2011-mortgage-loans-reach-record-volume-vedomosti-says.html
The volume of  mortgage loans  in
 Russia  reached a record high of 713 billion rubles ($24 billion)
last year as banks lowered rates,  Vedomosti  reported, citing
data from the central bank.  The result was an 88 percent increase from the previous
year and exceeded the earlier record of 655 billion rubles in
2008, the Moscow newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
